President Cyril Ramaphosa has lauded a new milestone in the tracking of the coronavirus outbreak in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has lauded a new milestone in the tracking of the coronavirus outbreak in South Africa. Ramaphosa visited a new data centre that will track the spread of the virus. COVID-19: WHO says SA can flatten curve Using real-time analytics and dashboards, the centre will be able to detail COVID-19 infections by province, district, local municipality, ward and even street. READ: Mkhize announces new directions in fight against COVID-19 The initiative is a collaboration between the departments of health, science and technology, and the Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR). The centre is housed in a secure facility at the CSIR in Pretoria. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.